args:
Volk suddenly flees, putting an end to the battle.
Outside the castle, Zethia is taken from Elisanne
by a mystery man. The prince falls into a deep
depression, but is comforted by the other
Zethia—now known as Zena—and swears
to rally from this latest loss.
*pant* *pant* We're out... Now to put\ndistance between us and the castle...
I will be taking the Auspex now.\nOr should I say, I will be taking\nmy younger sister.
Hmm? Did I just hear a bell?
The signal... But I still need to\nteach these cretins a lesson!
Alas, I fear my time has come.\nWe'll have to continue at a later date.
Wait, NOW you're gonna run off?!\nBetter rethink them plans, son!
Oh, you have it wrong... I'M the one\nwho won't let YOU people escape.
Were I you, I would spend my remaining\ndays fearing the bite of these fangs.\nBut for now, Ranzal...farewell.
Forget him! We need to find Zethia!
*pant* *pant* They should be...\nHuh? Wait, is that Elisanne?!
I'm glad you're all right, Elly,\nbut where's Zethia?
I am sorry... I am so, SO sorry...
A man appeared and...stole her away.
No... Not after we finally\nfreed her from the Other...
Might I sit with you a moment, Brother?
You must break free of this melancholy.\nEveryone is worried for you.
The Other is gone, and the capital freed.\nYour deeds have saved the lives of many.
You also made it possible for me\nto return to this world once more.
But I couldn't save Zethia. MY Zethia,\nI mean. She's gone—again.
I am so very sorry you must bear this pain.
There's no point in a peaceful world\nwithout Zethia in it.
Damn it all! If only I had been stronger!
Then we shall find her together.
Exactly that. Let us find your sister\nand see her returned to you safely.
It reminds me how your Zethia is currently\nilluminated by the selfsame moon,\nno matter how far away she may be.
And if we search for her,\nI know we can see her home.
...You're right. This is no time for moping.\nI need to act—I need to save her.
And I shall be with you every step of\nthe way.
Thank you. I'll be glad to have you.
Right, Zethia! Let's go save...um, Zethia?\nYeah, this is going to be confusing.
Heh. It will indeed. However, since I am\nnot of this world, it seems only right that\nI be the one to change my name.
Then what should we call you?
Zena... Heh. I like it.\nWelcome aboard, Zena.
I told the Paladyn woman we'd be waiting\nat the checkpoint of Alberia's north border.
The army of the false prince will never\ncome—they will be too busy wallowing\nin the despair of their own failure.
He will come. He will brave any danger\nfor the sake of his sister.
Tell the rest of Agito to gather here.\nI will set out ahead and proceed\nwith our preparations.
So Phares has made his move, eh?\nAnd the Ilian Church, too, won't ignore the\nchance this power vacuum represents.
The world is beginning to tilt on its axis,\nand a late start will not be tolerated.\nBut first...
You are my foe, {player_name},\nand I will teach you the difference\nbetween you and me.
